Cao <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uwiantwwcarbaonwsas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>wiantwwcarbaonwsas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/18/02 12:01:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22340.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The masters of melee damage - enchanters.</span><hr size=1> I tried something as an experiment.<br>
<br>
I'm a necromancer, I don't have dire charm (only level 58, in fact.)<br>
<br>
I grouped in the grey and kept a fallen iksar skeleton as a pet for about 2-3 hours, with normal charm.<br>
<br>
Sure, it broke on occasion, was easy enough to keep it charmed, I did not have any trouble with either mana cost of recharming, or taking damage from the skel beating on me (max hit 119).  I didn't need heals either (got only regen from group - but necro can keep themselves healed.)<br>
<br>
In a solo situation, I couldn't really have done this - when my pet would break, the mob it had been fighting would have gone for me and I would have had 2 on me.  Grouped, the mob we were fighting stayed on the melee that was tanking it.<br>
<br>
What people don't seem to realize is that this was *already* possible without Dire Charm.  Obviously, I don't want to see Dire Charm nerfed because I also get the skill - and I don't think anyone is going to say that dire charm is overpowering for druids and necros, given the general lack of undead / animal mobs.  But Boltran's Agacerie can charm mobs up to level *53*.  To give you some idea of what that is like.... Some of the dragon constructs in DN were even cons to me at 54.<br>
<br>
This was *already* possible by a careful enchanter.  All dire charm does is remove some of the danger of charm breaking, countered by the fact that you cannot charm as high level of a pet.  The issue (in Kael at least) is that Verant provides mobs that hit far, FAR too hard for their level.  Charm in Kael was responsible for pet nerfs before, because people were using charmed giants to tank (I will point out again that this was BEFORE dire charm was even in the game).  Now pets can't tank if there are PCs in melee range (sorry beastlords.)<br>
<br>
I really don't think Dire Charm is too powerful.  It is very good, admittedly, but I'd like to see that for all of the class-specific AA skills.  Some of them are ridiculously poor.  The strength of Dire Charm is in fact the same strength that Charm has - mobs have damage output and hps that are out of line with PCs at the same level.<br>
<br>
I have seen a bard solo a hill giant at level 27, *pre-kunark*, by sending in armies of charmed mobs to do the killing for them. <p>-Arbaon</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulucutos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lucutos</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/18/02 12:54:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22340.topic&index=35>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The masters of melee damage - enchanters.</span><hr size=1> Thank you Arbaon.  That was an excellent post and summation of the issues for me.<br>
<br>
I read about half of the original thread, and all of this thread and I wanted to be fired up about the whole thing too.  But what it all comes down to is the fact that even without Dire Charm - <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> it's all still possible!</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
I have to agree that charm is one of the most powerful spells in the game.  Charm, Harmony and Fear are all wickedly powerful in my opinion and I bet Verant has a hell of a time trying to code encounters around these spells. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
So anyway, grats enchanters - Hopefully Verant will try to come up with some great class abilities for the other classes.  A lot of them have great abilities already (SKs with Soul Abrasion and Horses, Paladins with their undead super hit thing and horses, plus Enchanters obviously) but it certainly wouldn't hurt to make sure everyone has at least one really cool, powerful ability they can strive for.<br>
<br>
Shregg - 39th Ogre Shadowknight <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showPrevMessage?topicID=22340.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showNextMessage?topicID=22340.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22340.topic&index=35><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.emailToFriend?topicID=22340.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.threadControl?topicID=22340.topic><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/dagger.jpg border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=22340.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=22340.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub35.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion">Main Lounge<option value="thesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc">News Bulletin<option value="thesafehousetrai